  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6590.54 sitting right between the massive negative gamma walls at 6580 (-27B) and 6590 (-26.5B), dealers are in full amplification mode and likely buying this breakout aggressively as they're forced to chase the move higher. The regime shift to BREAKOUT with -94.7B total GEX means any momentum will be mechanically amplified by dealer hedging flows, creating conditions for explosive moves in either direction. Key inflection point is the positive gamma wall at 6605 (+19.4B) where dealer selling pressure should kick in and provide meaningful resistance.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent upside momentum until 6605, then potential stall/reversal.",
